      "question": "If $4 \\tan \\theta = 3$, evaluate $\\frac{4 \\sin \\theta - \\cos \\theta}{4 \\sin \\theta + \\cos \\theta}$.",
      "answer": "\\frac{1}{2}",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Divide numerator and denominator by $\\cos \\theta$ to express in terms of $\\tan \\theta$.",
          "Substitute $\\tan \\theta = \\frac{3}{4}$ into the expression."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{4 \\sin \\theta / \\cos \\theta - 1}{4 \\sin \\theta / \\cos \\theta + 1} = \\frac{4 \\tan \\theta - 1}{4 \\tan \\theta + 1} \\\\ = \\frac{4(3/4) - 1}{4(3/4) + 1} = \\frac{3 - 1}{3 + 1} = \\frac{2}{4} = \\frac{1}{2}"
      },
